{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "DahnekeMassTransportCorrection",
        "description": "Correction factor β for diffusional mass transport to a sphere, valid across all Knudsen numbers from the continuum to the free-molecular regime (Dahneke 1983, Eq. 5.5). Computes the mean thermal velocity c̄, diffusional mean-free-path ℓ_D, diffusion Knudsen number Kn_D, and the correction factor β = (Kn_D+1)/(2Kn_D(Kn_D+1)/δ_m+1) as purely algebraic observed variables. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:33.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "dahneke",
            "mass-transport",
            "knudsen-number",
            "correction-factor",
            "transition-regime"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Aerosol.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-xn1)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Dahneke, B. (1983). Simple Kinetic Theory of Brownian Diffusion in Vapors and Aerosols. In Theory of Dispersed Multiphase Flow (pp. 97–133). Academic Press. Eqs. 3.6, 5.5, 6.2."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "DahnekeMassTransportCorrection": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Dahneke, B. (1983) Simple Kinetic Theory of Brownian Diffusion in Vapors and Aerosols, in Theory of Dispersed Multiphase Flow, Academic Press, pp. 97–133. Eqs. 3.6, 5.5, 6.2. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:33 @ c8c640bb (esm-xn1).",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb:src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:33\n\nUpstream DahnekeMassTransportCorrection is an MTK @component with 1 constant (k_B=1.380649e-23 J/K), 5 parameters (T, D_v, m_v, r, δ_m), and 4 algebraic variables determined by explicit equations with no time derivative — all purely observed.\n\nConstant k_B is folded as the floating-point literal 1.380649e-23, and π is folded as 3.14159265358979.\n\nEquation chain:\n  c_bar = sqrt(8 k_B T / (π m_v))              [mean thermal velocity, Eq. 6.2]\n  ℓ_D   = 2 D_v / c_bar                         [diffusional mean-free-path, Eq. 3.6]\n  Kn_D  = ℓ_D / r                               [diffusion Knudsen number]\n  β     = (Kn_D+1) / (2 Kn_D(Kn_D+1)/δ_m + 1) [mass transport correction, Eq. 5.5]\n\nLimiting cases:\n  Kn_D → 0: β → 1  (continuum limit, Maxwell's result)\n  Kn_D → ∞: β → δ_m c̄ r / (4 D_v)  (free-molecular limit)\n\nThe correction factor β relates the actual transport rate I to the continuum result I_M:\n  I = β I_M = β (4π r D_v (n_∞ - n_s))\n\nTopological evaluation order: T, m_v → c_bar → ℓ_D → Kn_D → β. The dependency graph is acyclic.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): purely algebraic system with sqrt, *, /, and + in float64. Round-off is ~1e-15 relative; rel=1e-9 leaves six orders of headroom above machine epsilon."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-9
            },
            "variables": {
                "T": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "K",
                    "default": 298.15,
                    "description": "Temperature. Default 298.15 K (25 °C), standard atmospheric."
                },
                "D_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^2/s",
                    "default": 2.0e-5,
                    "description": "Diffusion coefficient of vapor molecules. Default 2×10⁻⁵ m²/s (water vapor in air near 298 K)."
                },
                "m_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg",
                    "default": 4.81e-26,
                    "description": "Mass of diffusing vapor molecule. Default 4.81×10⁻²⁶ kg (water molecule, M=18 g/mol)."
                },
                "r": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1.0e-7,
                    "description": "Sphere (droplet/particle) radius. Default 100 nm — transition-regime aerosol."
                },
                "δ_m": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Condensation-evaporation (sticking) coefficient. Dimensionless; range (0, 1]. Default 1.0 (perfect accommodation). Smaller δ_m reduces β, reflecting partial reflection of vapor molecules at the particle surface."
                },
                "c_bar": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "description": "Mean thermal velocity of vapor molecules (Eq. 6.2): c̄ = sqrt(8 k_B T / (π m_v)). k_B = 1.380649×10⁻²³ J/K and π = 3.14159265358979 folded as literals.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "sqrt",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "/",
                                "args": [
                                    {"op": "*", "args": [8, 1.380649e-23, "T"]},
                                    {"op": "*", "args": [3.14159265358979, "m_v"]}
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "ℓ_D": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "m",
                    "description": "Diffusional mean-free-path of vapor molecules (Eq. 3.6): ℓ_D = 2 D_v / c̄. Characterises the length scale below which diffusive transport becomes ballistic.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {"op": "*", "args": [2, "D_v"]},
                            "c_bar"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "Kn_D": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Diffusion Knudsen number: Kn_D = ℓ_D / r. Dimensionless; Kn_D ≪ 1 means continuum diffusion dominates (β → 1); Kn_D ≫ 1 means free-molecular transport (β → δ_m c̄ r / (4 D_v)).",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": ["ℓ_D", "r"]
                    }
                },
                "β": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Mass transport correction factor (Eq. 5.5): β = (Kn_D+1) / (2 Kn_D(Kn_D+1)/δ_m + 1). Dimensionless; β = 1 in the continuum limit and β → δ_m c̄ r / (4 D_v) in the free-molecular limit. Multiplies the Maxwell (continuum) rate I_M to give the actual rate I = β I_M.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {"op": "+", "args": ["Kn_D", 1]},
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    1,
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    2,
                                                    "Kn_D",
                                                    {"op": "+", "args": ["Kn_D", 1]}
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "δ_m"
                                        ]
                                    }
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_conditions",
                    "description": "Default parameters: T=298.15 K, D_v=2e-5 m²/s, m_v=4.81e-26 kg, r=100 nm, δ_m=1.0. Checks the full equation chain: c̄=466.83 m/s, ℓ_D=85.68 nm, Kn_D=0.857 (transition regime), β=0.444.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "c_bar", "time": 0.0, "expected": 466.8276456276172,    "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "ℓ_D",   "time": 0.0, "expected": 8.568472834598901e-8, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "Kn_D",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.8568472834598901,   "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "β",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.4440020569957207,   "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "continuum_limit",
                    "description": "Large particle (r=100 µm): Kn_D = 8.57×10⁻⁴ ≪ 1, firmly continuum. β → 1 (within 0.1% of 1). Confirms the continuum limit of Eq. 5.5.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"r": 1.0e-4},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "Kn_D", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0008568472834598901, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "β",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.9991431539725586,    "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "free_molecular_limit",
                    "description": "Very small particle (r=0.1 nm): Kn_D = 856.8 ≫ 1, deep free-molecular regime. β ≈ δ_m c̄ r / (4 D_v) = 5.84×10⁻⁴ (asymptotic formula accurate to 0.001% at this Kn_D).",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"r": 1.0e-10},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "Kn_D", "time": 0.0, "expected": 856.84728345989,          "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "β",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.0005835341600963319,    "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "partial_accommodation",
                    "description": "Partial sticking coefficient δ_m=0.5 at default r=100 nm: β drops from 0.444 (δ_m=1) to 0.252, reflecting that half of vapor molecules are reflected rather than accommodated. Confirms δ_m enters only the denominator of Eq. 5.5.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"δ_m": 0.5},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "Kn_D", "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.8568472834598901,  "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "β",    "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.2521472618237901,  "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "temperature_200K",
                    "description": "Low temperature T=200 K: c̄ drops to 382.3 m/s, ℓ_D increases to 104.6 nm, Kn_D increases to 1.046 (more free-molecular), β falls to 0.387. Confirms the temperature dependence enters via c̄ ∝ √T and the resulting change in ℓ_D and Kn_D.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"T": 200.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "c_bar", "time": 0.0, "expected": 382.343893295089,   "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "Kn_D",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 1.0461786025997393, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "β",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.38743575347283044,"tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "temperature_400K",
                    "description": "High temperature T=400 K: c̄ rises to 540.7 m/s, ℓ_D decreases to 73.98 nm, Kn_D decreases to 0.740 (more continuum), β rises to 0.487. Confirms the temperature-β relationship reversal: higher T → shorter ℓ_D → smaller Kn_D → β closer to 1.",
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_overrides": {"T": 400.0},
                    "assertions": [
                        {"variable": "c_bar", "time": 0.0, "expected": 540.7159193884463,  "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "Kn_D",  "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.739759984230542,  "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}},
                        {"variable": "β",     "time": 0.0, "expected": 0.4867809997545371, "tolerance": {"rel": 1e-9}}
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "beta_vs_radius",
                    "description": "Correction factor β as a function of particle radius r (log sweep 0.1 nm to 10 µm) at T=298 K, D_v=2e-5 m²/s, m_v=4.81e-26 kg, δ_m=1. Shows the transition from the continuum limit (β→1 for large r) to the free-molecular limit (β→0 for small r), with the transition regime near r ~ ℓ_D ≈ 86 nm.",
                    "initial_state": {"type": "per_variable", "values": {}},
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "r",
                                "range": {"start": 1.0e-10, "stop": 1.0e-5, "count": 61, "scale": "log"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "beta_vs_r",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "β vs particle radius r. Shows the three regimes: free-molecular (small r, β→0), transition (r ~ ℓ_D), and continuum (large r, β→1).",
                            "x": {"variable": "r",    "label": "Particle radius r (m)"},
                            "y": {"variable": "β",    "label": "Mass transport correction factor β"}
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "beta_vs_delta_m",
                    "description": "Correction factor β as a function of sticking coefficient δ_m (linear sweep 0.01 to 1.0) at default r=100 nm. Illustrates how partial accommodation (δ_m < 1) suppresses β in the transition regime, with β → 0 as δ_m → 0 (no accommodation).",
                    "initial_state": {"type": "per_variable", "values": {}},
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": {"start": 0.0, "end": 1.0},
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "δ_m",
                                "range": {"start": 0.01, "stop": 1.0, "count": 50, "scale": "linear"}
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "beta_vs_delta_m_plot",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "β vs sticking coefficient δ_m for r=100 nm (transition regime). β increases monotonically with δ_m from near zero (specular reflection) to 0.444 (perfect accommodation).",
                            "x": {"variable": "δ_m", "label": "Sticking coefficient δ_m"},
                            "y": {"variable": "β",   "label": "Mass transport correction factor β"}
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
